The man was treated at the scene by paramedics and was taken to hospital. 

Paramedics tried to revive him but he died from his wounds.

Police from Bankstown Local Area Command and specialist forensic officers remain at the crime scene.

Detectives from the State Crime Command’s Homicide Squad are expected to aid in investigations into the shooting.

Authorities have been told a car drove from the scene shortly after the shooting. 

Police are urging anyone with information in relation to this incident to call Crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000 or use the Crime Stoppers online reporting page.

Information you provide will be treated in the strictest of confidence. 

